# Supplier Identification, Categorization & Criticality Assessment – Audit Checklist

## 1. Identification of Suppliers
- [ ] Has the organization identified and documented all of its suppliers, vendors, and other third-party service providers?

**Audit Evidence / Prüfpunkte:**
- Vollständige Supplier-Liste dokumentiert
- Genehmigung durch Management / Procurement
- Nachweis der Datenquelle(n) für Supplier-Informationen
- Historie der Aktualisierungen

---

## 2. Categorization & Prioritization
- [ ] How does the organization categorize and prioritize its suppliers based on their level of criticality to operations and cybersecurity risk exposure?

**Audit Evidence / Prüfpunkte:**
- Dokumentierte Kategorien (z. B. Critical, High, Medium, Low)
- Priorisierungsmethodik nachvollziehbar
- Berücksichtigung von Risikofaktoren (Datenzugriff, Business Impact)
- Mapping zu Risiko-Register oder ERM

---

## 3. Criteria for Criticality Assessment
- [ ] What criteria does the organization use to assess the criticality of its suppliers (e.g., access to sensitive data, impact on business continuity, cybersecurity controls)?

**Audit Evidence / Prüfpunkte:**
- Bewertungsmetriken dokumentiert
- Nachweis der Berücksichtigung von Datenschutz, Cybersecurity, BC/DR
- Risikoanalyse-Dokumente
- Management-Review-Protokolle

---

## 4. Roles & Responsibilities
- [ ] Are there clear roles and responsibilities assigned for the identification, categorization, and prioritization of suppliers based on criticality?

**Audit Evidence / Prüfpunkte:**
- RACI-Matrix oder Governance-Dokumentation
- Benannte Teams / Personen für Supplier Assessment
- Eskalations- und Freigabeprozesse dokumentiert
- Nachweis von Schulungen / Awareness

---

## 5. Periodic Review & Update
- [ ] How often does the organization review and update its supplier criticality assessments to account for changes in the supplier landscape and risk environment?

**Audit Evidence / Prüfpunkte:**
- Review-Zyklus dokumentiert (jährlich oder bei Bedarf)
- Protokolle von Review-Meetings
- Aktualisierte Supplier-Ratings
- Nachweis der Anpassung nach neuen Risiken

---

## 6. Alignment with Cybersecurity & ERM
- [ ] Does the organization's supplier criticality prioritization align with its overall cybersecurity and enterprise risk management strategies?

**Audit Evidence / Prüfpunkte:**
- Mapping zwischen Supplier-Criticality und Cybersecurity- / ERM-Strategien
- Management-Review-Dokumente
- Integration in Risk Registers
- Nachweis der Konsistenz mit Richtlinien

---

## 7. Communication of Criticality
- [ ] How does the organization communicate the criticality assessments and priorities to relevant internal and external stakeholders?

**Audit Evidence / Prüfpunkte:**
- Kommunikationsplan dokumentiert
- Mails, Workshops oder Reports an Stakeholder
- Nachweis der Kenntnisnahme
- Integration in Onboarding / Supplier Meetings

---

## 8. Monitoring & Validation
- [ ] Are there processes in place to monitor and validate the accuracy of the supplier criticality assessments over time?

**Audit Evidence / Prüfpunkte:**
- Kontinuierliche Monitoring-Prozesse dokumentiert
- Tools oder Reports zur Validierung
- Anpassungen basierend auf Feedback oder Vorfällen
- Nachweis von Management-Reviews

---

## 9. Centralized Repository
- [ ] Does the organization have a centralized repository or system to maintain and manage information on its suppliers and their criticality levels?

**Audit Evidence / Prüfpunkte:**
- Supplier Management System dokumentiert
- Zugriffskontrollen und Governance nachgewiesen
- Historie der Änderungen gespeichert
- Integration in Cybersecurity- und ERM-Prozesse
